## Fix: Display real Volume path in Documents section

**Context:** The Volume path banner in the Documents panel was showing an incorrect path — using dot notation (`catalog.schema.volume`) and omitting the version segment. The actual storage path follows the pattern `/Volumes/{catalog}/{schema}/{volume}/domains/{folder}/V{version}/documents`.

**Changes:**
1. `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-documents.js` — Fixed `loadVolumeLocation()` to build the path as `/Volumes/{catalog}/{schema}/{volume}/domains/{folder}/V{version}/documents`, using the `version` field already present in the `/domain/version-status` response.

**Modified files:**
- `src/front/static/domain/js/domain-documents.js`

**Test result:** N/A (frontend display fix, no unit tests affected)

