## Fix: Add Data Source — SP permission check and warning (GitHub issue #91)

Context: When the app service principal has USE CATALOG + USE SCHEMA but lacks
SELECT on source tables, SHOW TABLES silently returns an empty list, misleading
the user into thinking the schema contains no tables. Added two new probes that
detect missing READ TABLES (via information_schema) and missing SELECT (via
SELECT … LIMIT 0) and surface actionable warnings in the UI.

Changes:

1. src/back/core/databricks/UnityCatalog.py
   Added probe_schema_has_tables() — queries information_schema.tables (requires
   only USE SCHEMA) to detect hidden tables when SHOW TABLES returns empty.
2. src/back/core/databricks/UnityCatalog.py
   Added check_table_select_permission() — runs SELECT … LIMIT 0 on the first
   available table to confirm the SP can read data (not just metadata).
3. src/back/core/databricks/DatabricksClient.py
   Exposed probe_schema_has_tables() and check_table_select_permission() as
   facade methods on DatabricksClient.
4. src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py
   list_schema_tables_result() now calls both probes and returns a `permissions`
   dict with can_list_tables, can_select, hidden_table_count, and
   permission_warning fields.
5. src/front/static/domain/js/domain-metadata.js
   loadMetadataFromUC() surfaces permission_warning via showNotification when
   tables are empty (hard error) or SELECT is denied (soft warning).
   showTableSelectionModal() now accepts a perms argument and renders a
   per-permission badge banner (List tables: OK/denied, SELECT data: OK/denied).
6. src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_metadata.html
   Added #tableSelectionPermBanner alert div above the table list inside the
   Select Tables modal.

Modified files:
- src/back/core/databricks/UnityCatalog.py
- src/back/core/databricks/DatabricksClient.py
- src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py
- src/front/static/domain/js/domain-metadata.js
- src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_metadata.html

Tests: uv run pytest -q … -k "unity_catalog or metadata or permission" → 342 passed, 0 failed in 4.67s

