## Feature: Per-table SELECT permission column in Data Sources grid

Context: The schema-level SELECT probe added for issue #91 only tells the user
whether the service principal can read the *first* table of a schema during
import. Once tables are loaded, the Data Sources grid gave no per-table signal
of readability. Added a "Select" column to the loaded-tables grid showing, per
table, whether the app service principal can SELECT it — reusing the existing
SELECT … LIMIT 0 probe. Computed once at load/refresh time and persisted with
the table metadata.

Changes:

1. src/back/core/databricks/MetadataService.py
   _fetch_tables_metadata() now calls UnityCatalog.check_table_select_permission()
   per table and stores `can_select` (bool) and `select_error` (str|None) on
   each table dict; the error branch defaults can_select to False.
2. src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_metadata.html
   Added a "Select" <th> (dm-th-select-perm) between Cols and Description in the
   #metadataTablesTable header.
3. src/front/static/domain/js/domain-metadata.js
   displayMetadataPreview() renders a per-row badge via new renderSelectPermCell()
   helper: green check (can SELECT), red cross with the error as tooltip (denied),
   grey dash (unknown — metadata loaded before this field existed). Empty-state
   colspan bumped 5 → 6.
4. src/front/static/domain/css/domain-metadata.css
   Added .dm-th-select-perm (7%, centered) and rebalanced .dm-th-desc 51% → 44%.

Modified files:
- src/back/core/databricks/MetadataService.py
- src/front/templates/partials/domain/_domain_metadata.html
- src/front/static/domain/js/domain-metadata.js
- src/front/static/domain/css/domain-metadata.css

Tests: uv run pytest -q -k "metadata or unity_catalog or permission or select" →
362 passed, 1 failed (pre-existing MCP async event-loop smoke test, unrelated).
Full suite: 2987 passed, 58 failed — all failures pre-existing async event-loop
RuntimeErrors in unrelated api endpoint tests (review / version-status /
current-user / comments), none touched by this change.

