## Fix: Deployed app crash on v0.6.0 security bumps — pin lock to public CDN + `uv run --frozen`

**Context:** After landing the 24-advisory security sprint, the deployed app
reported "App started successfully" then immediately CRASHED. The container logs
(retrieved via `databricks apps logs ontobricks-060`) showed the true cause was
never native code or a runtime fault — it was a dependency *download* failure at
app start:

```
× Failed to download `python-multipart==0.0.32`
 ├─▶ Failed to fetch: https://pypi-proxy.dev.databricks.com/packages/.../python_multipart-0.0.32-py3-none-any.whl
 ├─▶ client error (Connect) ╰─▶ operation timed out
```

Root cause: the Databricks Apps base image defaults uv's index to the internal
`pypi-proxy.dev.databricks.com`. That proxy **cold-caches** — it had not yet
mirrored the freshly-published security wheels (python-multipart 0.0.32, etc.),
so the container's cold fetch through the proxy timed out and the process exited
before serving. The last-good deploy (a649625) worked only because every wheel
it needed was already warm in the proxy cache; the security bump introduced new
versions that were not. Each `uv lock` / `uv run` run locally rewrote every lock
URL back to the proxy (my `UV_INDEX_URL` points there), re-introducing the trap.

**Changes:**
1. `uv.lock` — Restored the full security version set (aiohttp 3.14.1,
   cryptography 48.0.1, msgpack 1.2.1, pyjwt 2.13.0, python-multipart 0.0.32,
   starlette 1.3.1, pydantic-settings 2.14.2, mlflow 3.14.0) and rewrote all
   3986 `pypi-proxy.dev.databricks.com` URLs to `files.pythonhosted.org`
   (wheels/sdists) and `pypi.org/simple` (registry) — the public CDN is always
   warm and reachable from the App container (same approach as commit cc84c98).
2. `pyproject.toml` — Removed the proxy-driven version caps and the `mlflow<3.12`
   cap added during the (incorrect) native-crash hypothesis; the native reverts
   were chasing a phantom, since the failure was a download timeout, not a fault.
3. `app.yaml.template` / `app.yaml` / `src/mcp-server/app.yaml` — Added
   `--frozen` to the `uv run` startup command. This makes uv use `uv.lock`
   verbatim and NEVER re-resolve in the container, so it cannot rewrite the
   pinned pythonhosted URLs back to the flaky proxy. Without `--frozen` the
   container's proxy-defaulted index would re-lock on startup and re-create the
   cold-cache timeout.

**Modified files:**
- `pyproject.toml`
- `uv.lock`
- `app.yaml.template`
- `app.yaml` (rendered)
- `src/mcp-server/app.yaml` (rendered)

**Test result:** `uv run --frozen pytest …` → 2787 passed, 28 skipped, 0 failed.
Verified `uv run --frozen` imports all security packages and leaves the lock at
0 proxy URLs (3653 files.pythonhosted.org + 333 pypi.org/simple).

