## Fix: MCP server pydantic-settings advisory (#60/#61) + same proxy/frozen treatment

**Context:** The MCP server pulled `pydantic-settings` transitively at 2.14.1,
leaving Dependabot #60/#61 (GHSA-4xgf-cpjx-pc3j — NestedSecretsSettingsSource
symlink traversal) unpatched in `src/mcp-server/uv.lock`. The MCP app was also
crashing on the same proxy cold-cache (`Failed to download aiofile==3.11.1` /
`exceptiongroup==1.3.1` → operation timed out).

**Changes:**
1. `src/mcp-server/pyproject.toml` — Added `[tool.uv] constraint-dependencies`
   pinning `pydantic-settings>=2.14.2` (transitive via fastmcp/databricks-sdk).
2. `src/mcp-server/uv.lock` — Re-locked (pydantic-settings 2.14.1 → 2.14.2) and
   rewrote all 1143 proxy URLs to files.pythonhosted.org / pypi.org.

**Modified files:**
- `src/mcp-server/pyproject.toml`
- `src/mcp-server/uv.lock`

**Test result:** `uv run --frozen mcp-ontobricks --help` → exit 0; lock at 0 proxy
URLs (1045 files.pythonhosted.org + 98 pypi.org/simple). Both apps RUNNING after
redeploy with clean startup logs (Uvicorn running, no download timeouts).
